11/07/2003
BANJA LUKA, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- On Friday (11 July), Republika Srpska Prime Minister Dragan Mikerevic is to attend a commemoration of the Srebrenica massacre, becoming the first senior Serb official to do so.
Also attending will be Deputy Prime Minister Omer Brankovic and Urbanisation Minister Mensur Sehagic, both Muslims;
Interior Minister Zoran Djeric, a Serb;
and Administration Minister Slaven Pekic, a Croat.Approximately 20,000 people are expected at the event, during which the remains of 282 victims will be laid to rest.
More than 7,000 Muslims were murdered at Srebrenica in 1995.
(BBC - 11/07/03;
AFP - 10/07/03)
